  "local_port": 42214,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I remove a non-friend from Facebook messenger contact list?",
  "response": "To remove a non-friend from your Facebook Messenger contact list, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open the Messenger app** on your device.\n\n2. **Go to the Chat List**:\n   - On the main screen, you should see a list of all your conversations and contacts.\n\n3. **Find the Contact**:\n   - Scroll through your chat list to find the non-friend you want to remove.\n\n4. **Open the Chat**:\n   - Tap on the conversation with the non-friend to open it.\n\n5. **Access Chat Settings**:\n   - **On Android**: Tap on the user\u2019s name at the top of the screen, then tap on the \"Info\" button (it looks like an \"i\" in a circle).\n   - **On iOS**: Tap on the user\u2019s name at the top of the screen, then tap on the \"Info\" button.\n\n6. **Block the Contact**:\n   - Scroll down and tap on \"Block\".\n   - Confirm that you want to block the contact by tapping \"Block\" again on the pop-up.\n\n7. **Remove the Contact**:\n   - After blocking, you'll be taken back to the chat. Tap on the user\u2019s name again and then tap on \"Block\" again.\n   - This time, you should see an option to \"Remove Contact\". Tap on it and confirm.\n\n**Important Notes:**\n- Removing a contact will delete your chat history with that person.\n- The person won't be notified that you've removed them, but they might notice if they try to message you again.\n- If you've blocked the person, they won't be able to message you until you unblock them.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to remove a non-friend from your Messenger contact list. If you face any issues or if the steps differ slightly due to app updates, you might need to refer to the latest Messenger help resources.",
